By John Woollam, CEO, Euphoria Telecom South African businesses are facing further economic hardship in the face of political uncertainty, ongoing load shedding, a rumoured VAT hike to 16% and generally slow economic conditions. Businesses looking to survive the downturn need to look to cost-containment while taking a strategic view on driving operational efficiencies and reducing capex. Your telephone system is a good place to start. Here we outline 5 tips which can help you to reduce your telephony costs this year. Whether it’s a business phone system or a call-centre solution you’re after, moving to digital, cloud-based telephony offers multiple benefits and can help businesses drive operational efficiencies and cut costs at a time when this is truly critical. This article was published in partnership with Euphoria.